cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about natural language understanding and dialogue generation using context-free grammars and deep learning.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of deep learning for conversational agents.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses sequence-to-sequence learning with LSTM RNNs.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is possible as the paper mentions the development of a tool for annotating nonterminal symbols in the grammar.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also possible as the paper discusses the use of the developed system in a videogame and its impact on gameplay.
